1
00:00:00,528 --> 00:00:08,628
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

2
00:00:08,803 --> 00:00:17,040
<i>Even if you get lost, let's start walking</i>

3
00:00:17,278 --> 00:00:19,269
<i>One more time</i>

4
00:00:22,283 --> 00:00:26,049
<i>Are you really happy</i>

5
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:29,487
<i>when you're always meeting</i>
<i>to someone's expectations?</i>

6
00:00:29,690 --> 00:00:33,251
<i>Even if you change to</i>
<i>who you really wanna be</i>

7
00:00:33,627 --> 00:00:36,994
<i>Will you always have a great smile?</i>

8
00:00:37,064 --> 00:00:44,493
<i>Dreaming of only "the beginning,"</i>
<i>I wake up</i>

9
00:00:44,572 --> 00:00:53,708
<i>and someday, I'll live on my own.</i>

10
00:00:53,781 --> 00:01:01,813
<i>Yes, precious things are never in shape</i>

11
00:01:02,056 --> 00:01:08,894
<i>You never know what it is</i>
<i>when you get it or lose it</i>

12
00:01:08,963 --> 00:01:17,029
<i>Yeah, turn your sadness into kindness,</i>
<i>your uniqueness into strength</i>

13
00:01:17,338 --> 00:01:25,803
<i>Even if you get lost,</i>
<i>let's start walking</i>

14
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:27,905
<i>One more time</i>

15
00:01:58,356 --> 00:02:00,347
<i>That darn Naruto...</i>

16
00:02:01,393 --> 00:02:07,263
<i>Zero Motivation.</i>
<i>The Guy with Cloud Envy!</i>

17
00:02:07,465 --> 00:02:09,729
- C'mon!
- Hurry up with the match!

18
00:02:10,001 --> 00:02:11,059
Finish it up already!

19
00:02:13,939 --> 00:02:15,031
Stand up and start the match!

20
00:02:19,377 --> 00:02:25,805
<i>Evidently, people don't want to</i>
<i>see the minor players matches</i>

21
00:02:25,884 --> 00:02:29,115
<i>since they were really looking</i>
<i>forward to Sasuke's match...</i>

22
00:02:30,388 --> 00:02:33,619
<i>If people aren't expecting anything</i>
<i>exciting from this battle,</i>

23
00:02:33,692 --> 00:02:35,819
<i>makes no sense</i>
<i>for me to have it.</i>

24
00:02:37,629 --> 00:02:40,530
What? You're giving up, too?

25
00:02:43,034 --> 00:02:44,899
<i>My opponent's a girl again?</i>

26
00:02:46,271 --> 00:02:47,465
Hey, why aren't you moving

27
00:02:47,606 --> 00:02:49,471
C'mon, get started!

28
00:02:50,175 --> 00:02:53,440
<i>That kid has had zero fighting spirit</i>
<i>from the beginning...</i>

29
00:02:53,845 --> 00:02:56,370
C'mon! What is he doing?!

30
00:02:56,715 --> 00:03:00,583
C'mon Shikamaru!
Get it together and do it!

31
00:03:04,222 --> 00:03:06,019
If you don't come, I'll go!

32
00:03:06,524 --> 00:03:08,515
Hey! Haven't started yet...

33
00:03:08,727 --> 00:03:12,925
Man, that girl is so gung ho.

34
00:03:30,048 --> 00:03:34,678
It doesn't really matter if
I become a Chunin or not.

35
00:03:35,453 --> 00:03:38,889
But there's no reason why
a man should lose to a woman.

36
00:03:40,392 --> 00:03:42,087
Well... let's do it!

37
00:03:58,977 --> 00:04:00,842
<i>This guy's quick to run away...</i>

38
00:04:05,483 --> 00:04:09,385
<i>Nor any reason why a man should</i>
<i>rough up a woman.</i>

39
00:04:11,056 --> 00:04:12,751
<i>But I don't want to be</i>
<i>roughed up either.</i>

40
00:04:14,025 --> 00:04:16,516
<i>He's the kind of Ninja that</i>
<i>uses shadows.</i>

41
00:04:17,362 --> 00:04:18,659
<i>Shadow Possession Jutsu.</i>

42
00:04:25,737 --> 00:04:28,865
<i>He's probably trying to lure me into</i>
<i>the trees where there're lots of shadows...</i>

43
00:04:29,574 --> 00:04:30,700
<i>but I won't let him.</i>

44
00:04:31,543 --> 00:04:35,240
<i>Why am I the only one who always</i>
<i>gets a woman for an opponent, cripes?!</i>

45
00:04:35,847 --> 00:04:42,116
Shikamaru! You get her with
a torrent of 16 combination...!

46
00:04:44,055 --> 00:04:45,716
Mind if I sit here?

47
00:04:45,924 --> 00:04:46,583
Huh?

48
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:50,617
What... you?
Your stomach okay?

49
00:04:54,766 --> 00:04:57,997
What? Wasn't Sasuke's match next?

50
00:04:58,570 --> 00:04:59,298
Shh!

51
00:05:02,006 --> 00:05:06,306
Everything's fine, right, Sakura?
After all, it's Sasuke, right?

52
00:05:08,079 --> 00:05:10,639
<i>R-Right now, I should leave her alone.</i>

53
00:05:12,016 --> 00:05:14,484
It looks like Shikamaru taking part
in this final battle,

54
00:05:14,853 --> 00:05:16,548
it seems like he's in the wrong place.

55
00:05:16,955 --> 00:05:18,445
Don't say that!

56
00:05:18,823 --> 00:05:22,122
I certainly don't think that
he has any great techniques,

57
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:26,196
but that Shikamaru is
always good at strategizing.

58
00:05:26,865 --> 00:05:31,393
That's why I feel like we ended up
in the preliminary round the other day.

59
00:05:31,936 --> 00:05:33,767
Hmm, yeah well...

60
00:05:33,972 --> 00:05:37,066
And after all, he jumped down
into the arena himself.

61
00:05:38,143 --> 00:05:41,044
He seems uncharacteristically driven.

62
00:05:41,513 --> 00:05:44,311
Even he can be passionate
once in a while!

63
00:05:44,783 --> 00:05:47,411
Go! Shikamaru!

64
00:05:49,854 --> 00:05:55,053
<i>Geez, I envy a cloud being so free...</i>

65
00:05:59,431 --> 00:06:03,231
<i>I guess I pretty much</i>
<i>am completely without desire...</i>

66
00:06:03,868 --> 00:06:05,733
<i>Even the reason why I became a Ninja...</i>

67
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:09,738
<i>was because I thought</i>
<i>I would have a fun life, ya know...</i>

68
00:06:18,316 --> 00:06:20,113
Get it together!

69
00:06:20,185 --> 00:06:22,016
C'mon Shikamaru!

70
00:06:26,057 --> 00:06:30,084
<i>But...of course, it's not that easy.</i>

71
00:06:30,795 --> 00:06:33,958
What's going on with that stupid face?!
Is he underestimating me?

72
00:06:34,532 --> 00:06:35,999
Ninja Art: Wind Scythe Jutsu!

73
00:06:49,113 --> 00:06:54,073
<i>That's right, with this attack,</i>
<i>my armed attacks also were beaten down.</i>

74
00:07:13,805 --> 00:07:14,772
I see...

75
00:07:21,212 --> 00:07:24,204
Shadow Possession Jutsu!
I've seen that true identity!

76
00:07:25,116 --> 00:07:27,641
Evidently there's a limit to
the stretching and shortening

77
00:07:27,886 --> 00:07:30,218
changing shape of the shadow...

78
00:07:31,356 --> 00:07:32,789
No matter how much you
change the shape of the shadow,

79
00:07:32,857 --> 00:07:33,789
even when you stretch it,

80
00:07:34,192 --> 00:07:37,593
it can only span up to
the size of your own shadow.

81
00:07:38,997 --> 00:07:39,588
That's right isn't it?

82
00:07:41,699 --> 00:07:42,563
You got it...

83
00:07:43,902 --> 00:07:46,564
<i>Even if I assume that he's made up</i>
<i>the distance,</i>

84
00:07:46,638 --> 00:07:50,165
<i>by stretching his shadow from the edge</i>
<i>of the shadow of the arena wall...</i>

85
00:07:51,209 --> 00:07:53,200
<i>This is the limit to how far</i>
<i>the shadow can stretch.</i>

86
00:07:54,779 --> 00:07:56,747
<i>This is the scope of his attack!</i>

87
00:07:58,249 --> 00:08:00,444
<i>15 meters, 32 centimeters!</i>

88
00:08:01,386 --> 00:08:03,354
<i>She took the distance</i>
<i>with the folding fan.</i>

89
00:08:04,422 --> 00:08:07,289
<i>Temari is stronger at long distance</i>
<i>battles than she is at close range...</i>

90
00:08:08,159 --> 00:08:10,218
<i>the outcome has already been decided.</i>

91
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:37,788
What? What is that sign...?

92
00:08:39,324 --> 00:08:43,761
That's no sign. That's like, his habit.

93
00:08:44,362 --> 00:08:45,090
Habit?

94
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:52,627
He enjoys passing time slowly.
That guy's like an old man.

95
00:08:53,237 --> 00:08:55,364
That's why he likes
Japanese checkers and chess

96
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:58,370
and always makes me be his opponent.

97
00:09:03,948 --> 00:09:06,940
When he's stuck on a move,
he always does that.

98
00:09:14,258 --> 00:09:15,247
Why?

99
00:09:16,427 --> 00:09:18,292
He's working out his strategy.

100
00:09:26,871 --> 00:09:30,432
And, I've never beaten him.

101
00:09:31,743 --> 00:09:34,678
A strategy...
but this is an actual fight.

102
00:09:34,979 --> 00:09:36,503
It's different from a game.

103
00:09:37,015 --> 00:09:40,178
But it's said that formation pieces
that were used to build battle strategy

104
00:09:40,251 --> 00:09:42,481
eventually become
game pieces.

105
00:09:43,254 --> 00:09:46,553
Shikamaru is like a brilliant general.

106
00:09:47,225 --> 00:09:48,249
Wait a minute.

107
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:51,920
When we grouped the Genin,
I saw his scores.

108
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:55,058
They were at about the
same level of that Naruto's.

109
00:09:55,767 --> 00:09:59,965
He said that moving his pencil during
written exams at the academy is a pain,

110
00:10:00,338 --> 00:10:02,636
and during the tests,
he always sleeps instead.

111
00:10:03,074 --> 00:10:03,733
A pain...?

112
00:10:20,058 --> 00:10:24,222
He was so good at strategy games,
I felt something wasn't right...

113
00:10:25,129 --> 00:10:28,963
so I had him take an IQ test
under the pretense that it was a game.

114
00:10:34,672 --> 00:10:36,606
And... how did it turn out?...

115
00:10:41,412 --> 00:10:42,936
He was more than brilliant.

116
00:10:43,981 --> 00:10:47,439
With an IQ of over 200,
he's a super genius!

117
00:10:48,953 --> 00:10:50,614
T-Two hundred?!

118
00:10:58,529 --> 00:11:01,430
<i>He's done thinking...</i>
<i>It starts now.</i>

119
00:11:13,946 --> 00:11:16,073
Looks like you've got some
fighting spirit now...

120
00:11:26,926 --> 00:11:28,188
It's pointless to hide!

121
00:11:35,601 --> 00:11:37,728
I wonder if he's really got a strategy...

122
00:11:38,771 --> 00:11:40,136
M-Maybe...

123
00:11:48,647 --> 00:11:50,740
With that he has no approach!

124
00:11:51,317 --> 00:11:53,148
Shikamaru! Go for it!

125
00:11:53,819 --> 00:11:55,184
It's pointless, isn't it?

126
00:11:55,421 --> 00:11:57,412
He'll give up soon.

127
00:11:57,489 --> 00:11:58,979
He hates things
that are a pain in the butt.

128
00:11:59,158 --> 00:12:03,012
You're wrong!
At least, I hope so...

129
00:12:03,195 --> 00:12:05,356
But you may be right...

130
00:12:38,764 --> 00:12:42,131
How long are you going to run away!
Cut it out!

131
00:12:53,312 --> 00:12:53,971
<i>It's no use.</i>

132
00:12:54,446 --> 00:12:56,141
<i>As long as I'm on the</i>
<i>outside of this line,</i>

133
00:12:56,215 --> 00:12:57,614
<i>he absolutely can't catch me...</i>

134
00:12:58,717 --> 00:13:00,776
<i>No, wait! Close call!</i>

135
00:13:09,662 --> 00:13:11,027
You caught on well.

136
00:13:11,830 --> 00:13:14,663
So you were dragging your feet
to wait for the sun to set...

137
00:13:15,701 --> 00:13:17,362
in order to make the surface
of your own shadow larger

138
00:13:17,636 --> 00:13:20,400
by stretching the shadow line of the wall.

139
00:13:22,841 --> 00:13:24,706
As the sun goes down,
the shadows lengthen.

140
00:13:25,678 --> 00:13:26,610
Isn't that so?

141
00:13:31,517 --> 00:13:33,542
That was close! Shikamaru...

142
00:13:33,986 --> 00:13:36,750
But why is he using shadows?

143
00:13:36,922 --> 00:13:40,323
After all, Shikamaru is inside
the shadow of the field.

144
00:13:40,726 --> 00:13:44,753
If there's even a little bit of light,
he can make a shadow within a shadow!

145
00:13:45,097 --> 00:13:48,191
You don't know a thing
about Shikamaru!

146
00:13:49,401 --> 00:13:52,131
A shadow... in a shadow...?

147
00:14:01,747 --> 00:14:03,772
<i>Even if I calculate the height</i>
<i>of the sun now</i>

148
00:14:03,882 --> 00:14:06,578
<i>and the limit to the distance</i>
<i>of the previous attack,</i>

149
00:14:07,319 --> 00:14:09,879
<i>there's no mistaking the distance!</i>

150
00:14:18,497 --> 00:14:20,192
Temari! Up!

151
00:14:22,067 --> 00:14:22,863
I see.

152
00:14:24,503 --> 00:14:25,333
<i>What's this?!</i>

153
00:14:28,941 --> 00:14:29,669
Darn it!

154
00:14:43,188 --> 00:14:44,314
I won't let you escape!

155
00:14:48,093 --> 00:14:50,152
<i>I didn't expect that he would</i>
<i>create extra shadows to reach me</i>

156
00:14:50,229 --> 00:14:51,924
<i>by making a parachute with his jacket...!</i>

157
00:14:55,367 --> 00:14:56,561
<i>He's impressive.</i>

158
00:14:57,402 --> 00:15:01,395
<i>Once I notice the parachute from above,</i>
<i>I'll take my attention off from my feet.</i>

159
00:15:02,007 --> 00:15:04,601
<i>That's a sneaky trick to catch me</i>
<i>off my guard!</i>

160
00:15:05,244 --> 00:15:07,337
<i>However, now it's clear.</i>

161
00:15:08,147 --> 00:15:09,444
<i>Shadow Possession Jutsu is</i>

162
00:15:09,915 --> 00:15:13,214
<i>one in which other shadows are used</i>
<i>to get your opponent,</i>

163
00:15:13,385 --> 00:15:14,750
<i>a skillful technique!</i>

164
00:15:28,834 --> 00:15:30,893
She's dodged this trick too...

165
00:15:31,470 --> 00:15:32,835
Not careful enough in the final stage.

166
00:15:34,373 --> 00:15:36,603
And his opponent is fairly analytical.

167
00:15:37,309 --> 00:15:38,833
She's good at thinking ahead.

168
00:15:46,652 --> 00:15:48,119
<i>If this battle takes too long,</i>

169
00:15:48,253 --> 00:15:51,950
<i>the shadows in the arena will grow,</i>
<i>and his territory will increase.</i>

170
00:15:57,062 --> 00:15:58,324
<i>I'll defeat him with the next one!</i>

171
00:15:59,598 --> 00:16:02,567
<i>Should I make a diversion</i>
<i>with Clone Jutsu...?</i>

172
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:13,478
<i>Now his shadow is...</i>

173
00:16:15,681 --> 00:16:16,079
<i>Okay!</i>

174
00:16:19,151 --> 00:16:20,140
Clone...

175
00:16:23,589 --> 00:16:24,817
<i>N-No way...!</i>

176
00:16:30,562 --> 00:16:33,588
<i>My... body is...?!</i>

177
00:16:38,303 --> 00:16:41,795
At last...
Shadow Possession Jutsu is a success!

178
00:16:42,674 --> 00:16:43,299
<i>What?!</i>

179
00:16:49,648 --> 00:16:50,842
What's going on...?

180
00:16:51,516 --> 00:16:52,278
That boy...

181
00:16:53,118 --> 00:16:55,382
How much is he planning ahead...?

182
00:16:56,321 --> 00:16:58,619
That's Shikamaru's skill.

183
00:16:59,591 --> 00:17:02,185
<i>Why...won't my body move?!</i>

184
00:17:03,195 --> 00:17:05,095
<i>The shadow shouldn't</i>
<i>have reached this far.</i>

185
00:17:07,933 --> 00:17:09,992
I'll let you take a look behind you...

186
00:17:20,245 --> 00:17:21,303
<i>T-This hole...!</i>

187
00:17:22,614 --> 00:17:24,206
You saw it too, didn't you...?

188
00:17:25,617 --> 00:17:29,280
That hole is the hole Naruto
burrowed and flew out of.

189
00:17:30,789 --> 00:17:34,555
So it's connected to the
big hole in front of you.

190
00:17:36,828 --> 00:17:40,628
I didn't expect that...
a shadow in a tunnel of a hole...

191
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:42,857
Right.

192
00:17:44,236 --> 00:17:46,932
Pure and simple,
a calculated chess move.

193
00:17:54,980 --> 00:17:58,541
<i>So his purpose to make Temari measure</i>
<i>the limit of the shadow several times</i>

194
00:17:59,017 --> 00:18:03,078
<i>was to lead her to his final trick</i>
<i>of using this hole.</i>

195
00:18:07,993 --> 00:18:10,291
<i>Temari battled on the outside</i>
<i>of the limit of the shadow</i>

196
00:18:10,362 --> 00:18:12,455
<i>that she measured and followed,</i>

197
00:18:12,998 --> 00:18:19,904
<i>but he caught her from behind,</i>
<i>trailed by the shadow she couldn't see...</i>

198
00:18:20,539 --> 00:18:22,473
<i>There is no escape from this.</i>

199
00:18:23,041 --> 00:18:24,565
<i>I-It can't be...</i>

200
00:18:26,912 --> 00:18:29,403
<i>The attack that he used</i>
<i>with the jacket,</i>

201
00:18:30,215 --> 00:18:33,343
<i>was it a device to lead me</i>
<i>to right this spot...?</i>

202
00:18:35,087 --> 00:18:36,384
<i>Was that an underplot too?!</i>

203
00:18:38,790 --> 00:18:39,518
<i>Why that?!</i>

204
00:18:40,959 --> 00:18:42,688
Checkmate with the next one.

205
00:18:51,003 --> 00:18:54,530
<i>My body is moving on its own!</i>
<i>I can't resist it!</i>

206
00:19:07,185 --> 00:19:10,518
Before anyone knew it,
they fell under the spell of this match.

207
00:19:10,789 --> 00:19:14,281
That guy with no mark
is quite a darkhorse.

208
00:19:14,493 --> 00:19:17,826
Yes! You did it!

209
00:19:17,896 --> 00:19:20,456
Go! Shikamaru!

210
00:19:24,169 --> 00:19:25,033
Check...

211
00:19:55,934 --> 00:19:58,334
Good grief... I give up!

212
00:20:07,679 --> 00:20:08,805
What?!

213
00:20:13,985 --> 00:20:17,182
See I told you... he'd give up.

214
00:20:18,457 --> 00:20:22,154
Ino doesn't know anything
about Shikamaru.

215
00:20:22,727 --> 00:20:24,490
W-What did you say?!

216
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:31,864
I've used too much Chakra from Shadow
Possession Jutsu in rapid succession.

217
00:20:31,937 --> 00:20:33,962
I can't hold it another 10 seconds.

218
00:20:36,308 --> 00:20:40,074
I thought of the next trick 200 times.

219
00:20:40,812 --> 00:20:42,677
But I'm out of time...

220
00:20:47,185 --> 00:20:49,050
This has become such a pain.

221
00:20:49,254 --> 00:20:50,846
Doing one match is good...

222
00:20:53,658 --> 00:20:55,091
<i>That guy is a strange one.</i>

223
00:20:56,428 --> 00:20:58,328
The winner is Temari!

224
00:21:12,044 --> 00:21:15,411
<i>One! First, Tyson jumps and slamdunks</i>

225
00:21:15,481 --> 00:21:18,814
<i>Two! He kisses and hugs everyone</i>
<i>randomly and says "I LOVE YOU"</i>

226
00:21:18,885 --> 00:21:22,321
<i>Three! Masala masters Yoga</i>
<i>but hates curry</i>

227
00:21:22,388 --> 00:21:25,619
<i>Four! Sanchez is a lousy bullfighter. Ole!</i>

228
